From 94c2922c132095e4a6b3de1b5f3444f1623af831 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 2026 23:37:41 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 021/174] PGCL: riscv64 boot with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4 + cross-arch
 PTE portability

Fix PTE sub-page offset encoding for architectures where the PTE PFN
field shift differs from MMUPAGE_SHIFT (riscv: _PAGE_PFN_SHIFT=10 vs
MMUPAGE_SHIFT=12).  All raw PTE arithmetic that added N*MMUPAGE_SIZE
directly to pte_val now wraps with __phys_to_pte_val(), which is the
identity on x86 but performs (phys>>12)<<10 on riscv.

Add generic __phys_to_pte_val fallback (identity) in linux/pgtable.h
so architectures that don't override it (x86, arm, etc.) get correct
default behavior.

Fix pgcl_pte_batch() sub-page index extraction: use division by the
PTE-encoded MMUPAGE step size instead of raw bit shifting, making it
portable across all PTE formats.

Fix riscv pageattr.c split_linear_mapping PFN stride bugs (3 fixes)
in PUD->PMD and PMD->PTE page table splits.

Full riscv64 arch PGCL adaptation: page table definitions, TLB flush,
hugepage, hibernation, kasan, context, fixmap, all using MMUPAGE_SHIFT
where hardware page granularity is needed.

Remove all 39 PGCL-DEBUG prints and re-enable POISON_FREE_INITMEM.

Tested: x86_64 PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4 boots SMP=4 all tests PASS
        riscv64 PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4 boots SMP=4 all tests PASS

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
